						<h2 class="mt-4" id="definition">Tailspin: The Feedback Loop</h2>
						<blockquote>
							<p>“You are not stuck in traffic. You are traffic.”</p>
							<p>— TomTom SatNav Advertisement</p>
						</blockquote>
						<p class="shout-out">Multiplayer tailspin is a phenomenon where a declining player count in a game causes a feedback loop where additional players abandon the title due to a declining population.</p>
						<p>We’ve all been part of it, whether we know it or not. We’ve all been partly responsible for killing our favourite games.</p>
						<p>Tailspin happens when the declining population of a game in terms fuels a further loss of players, worsening as more people stop playing.</p>
						<p>Tailspin affects both players and developers.</p>
						<!-- Wide Image — With Caption -->
					</div>
					<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 my-4">
