						<h2 class="mt-4">How Tailspin killed Titanfall 2</h2>
						<p>Whenever I do venture back to play Titanfall 2, I’m often met with two major issues.</p>
						<p>First: the waiting.</p>
						<p>When a game’s population spirals like this, the wait for a match can be agonising. Time is valuable, so sitting for ten minutes between matches just watching a timer tick up is not my idea of fun.</p>
						<p>Second: the skill gap.</p>
						<p>With a population this low, most of the people still playing are good. Really, really good.</p>
						<p>A combination of fast-paced movement, very low health, countless weapons, maps, and pieces of equipment to learn means the new player experience in Titanfall 2 can be especially harsh.</p>
						<p>Even as a returning player I become frustrated as I am outpaced by players with far more hours of practice.</p>
						<p>This sort of massive skill barrier isn’t a good incentive to get players to return to a game after a long break, or for new players to want to try it out.</p>
